The paper is about a challenge related to oriental language recognition, which involves speech processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The challenge also focuses on short-duration utterances, confusing languages, and open-set recognition, which are related to speech and audio processing, and could fall under cs.SD (Sound). The challenge also involves the use of i-vector models and neural networks, which are machine learning techniques, and could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper reports baseline results on the three tasks, which could fall under cs.SD.
